<h2>World Tracking</h2>
<p>
  ARKit uses a world tracking configuration to detect real-world surfaces. In order to establish world tracking, ARKit must 
  first get a sense of perspective. Such a sense of perspective can be established by moving the device's camera throughout
  the world space, using an ARKit interface named <i>ARCoachingOverlayView</i> to instruct the user to explore the physical and
  build a virtual sense of reference.
</p>
