<h2>Focus Square</h2>
<p>
  To get an idea of where to place virtual content in the world space, a focus square is annotated onto the screen. The primary 
  purpose of the focus square is to give a visual confirmation of the shapes, alignments and surfaces detected by ARKit. To detect 
  surfaces, ARKit uses an <i>ARRaycastQuery</i>, defining where the 3D location in the world space exists as a 2D point on the device screen.
</p>
<center>
  <%= image_tag "FocusSquare.png", :class => "style_image", :size => "450x320" %>
