<h2>Gestures</h2>
<p>
  A pan gesture recognizer allows users to move virtual content on screen. By clicking and dragging a virtual object, the application 
  calculates the content's orientation information and uses a <i>hit test</i> to refine the position of the object in the world. What 
  results is a refined virtual object that moves across the plane detected by ARKit.
</p>
